caption: Delivery was fast and food was hot! 1 star. Food was plentiful, another star. Food was greasy, tasteless and old. There were six pieces of shrimp  in my fried rice. The fried chicken wings were not fried, it was more or less baked and odd tasting. First and last time.
Chicken lo mein special came with an egg roll. Portion size was medium but i was only charged $8. If you have a craving for Chinese food, it’s worth a try.

Best food I've ever had and will ever have. This is not your usual chinese restaurant. They have 2 of the best dishes ever. The jalapeño chicken and the mabo tofu are absolutely freaking delicious. So sad I cant come here anymore.
Good food
Reliable ok food. Never got sick.
Excellent food. Definitely recommend the dumplings

This is your run of the mill average Chinese place that you go to when you’re too hungover to even cook any bacon. The fried rice WILL hit the spot with the umami flavors and any of the dishes will definitely soak up any left over alcohol. Don’t expect gourmet. This place gets it done when you need that greasy spoon Chinese fill.
The worst assortment of items ever. Chicken nuggets (supposed to be sweet and sour chicken) . Never again
Jalapeno chicken is to die for and beef fried rice was bomb dot com.

If I could give this place 0 stars I would have. This was my 1st time ordering from them and my experience was horrible. They are  extremely rude. I paid $3 for extra shrimp that was not there. I called about my order to ask how many shrimps did I get and they said 8. I only counted 4. When I informed the person on the phone she told me "you calling my cook a liar". At that point I was like I see what type of business you run. I was not about to argue over 4 pieces of shrimp.  Never order from this place.  A waste of time unless you want to be treated rudely.
Great food but i need to know if you guys are open and the phone number
Food is always great and prices are very reasonable. I love the hot and sour soup that comes with a $20 order!
Owners are very nice food is always hot they have big portions for the money. They have great lunch specials food is always good.
GOOD CUSTOMER SERVICE... HORRIBLE  FOOD EGG ROLLS  & FRIED CRAB  RAGOON NOT DELICIOUS 👎👎👎👎 WORST FOOD EVER. WANT MY $$$ REFUNED...
Food Excelente!!

The eggrolls were bland and not well fried. The general tso chicken was a big, sticky mess with too much batter and sauce. The egg food young was a yucky, fried mess. The combination fried rice was edible. I wouldn't eat here again.
The place serves big dishes and for fair rates. very nice employees. 5 stars.
(Translated by Google) Nice quiet  (Original) Tranquilo agradable
The food is very good but the customer service is pretty bad. The lady at the counter did not want to answer any questions about the dishes and was rude and impatient.
Good food!
Delicious food not a very long wait time and the people are really friendly.
Great Chinese food. Had the salt and pepper fish fillet, fish was firm and nicely fried.
Good service and tasted food. Had different dishes for couple of times, they were all good. Try their orange chicken, my favorite.
Just ordered fried rice The pork was lean and tasty

This placed used to be a go-to for us, but in the last year (2018-2019), the quality of the food has become very inconsistent. But we won't be ordering from them again after one of their drivers tried to extort more money from us.

Worst Chinese food I have ever had. Orange chicken was soggy and smelled like dog food. Had barely any flavor and clumps of sugar in the sauce. I got the appetizer platter so I could try a variety. What a waste. The beef skewers were chewy no flavor. Egg rolls tasted like refrigerator and old too. Chewy and soggy on the outside. Wasn’t fried properly. As someone who cooks for a living, spend your money somewhere that cares about its food. This place does not.
Food is great !

Reasonable price and flavorful food. Hot and soup soup was good, fried rice was not try and had multiple ingredients not just the opinion. I loved how they prepared the salt and pepper squid and aged amazing! Also liked their smoothie, very refreshing.

Passed by this place for lunch. Great deal and good food. The Mongolian beef was different but tasted really good, all the people ordered before me got Mongolian beef so I divided to try this dish and it turned out to be my new favorite dish. My little one loved their fried rice, good tasted  and he ate it all! Will order again.

Not what it used to be!! I can't believe my vegetable fried rice had frozen veggies in it! That's really terrible and lazy on their part. Orange chicken was all hard breading and my egg roll was so dry it tasted like rolled up paper towels. I'm very serious and I had a 3 dollar delivery charge when the driver came he had NO change for me. Unbelievable, very very disappointed don't waste your money!

Ordered the salt and pepper shrimp which was the best I've ever had in town.  Amount of food was generous and the flavor was wonderful. My wife likes their combo fried rice, the small size was good for her little stomach. And my daughter looooooooove their sweet and sour chicken. Their delivery was fast and always a pro.

I ordered from here about a month ago, unfortunately after placing the order I realized I only had a $100.00 bill. The delivery driver, instead of going back to the restaurant (which was 2.5 mi, 10 minutes or under from my place) and getting change or trying to help figure out a way for me to receive the correct amount of change he took my $100, handed me back $23, told me he had no more chage and left. Keep in mind my total was only $30.  He gave himself nearly a $50 dollar tip (forgive me if my math is incorrect).  Also, I get it, I should not expect all diverlery drivers to walk around with that amount of change but considering that he worked for the restaurant he could have kept the food, got the change and come back...I would rather wait until he makes his other deliveries and have cold food than pay $77 for $30 worth of subpar orange chicken.  I followed up with the restaurant, they told me they would speak to the driver and follow up with me about my refund and guess what?....I never heard from them again.  I would not recommended this place at all based on that AND to be honest the food wasn't very good.
Great food and service.
Good food

Ordered the lunch special- jalapeno chicken & mongolian beef. The jalapeno chicken was so good, but the mogolian beef looked very different from other places but it was still okay. For $6.55 you get a great portion, and either egg roll or soda.

Hot and sour soup was a hit. The Mongolian beef was different than anywhere else but tasted really good. Meat was rendered and Nicely flavored. The only disappointment was they don’t have parking, but the girl works in the front usually bring my food to my car. How nice is that!! Anyway, I always order take out.

I ordered Crispy Chow Mein after having this dish at many different restaurants and, instead of chow mien noodles, I'm pretty sure they gave me a bag of crispy wontons you put on top of a salad. Extremely dissapointed.
Great food for a good price and fast service.
very nice staff (:

I was very disappointed. Orange chicken lunch special was terrible. Mostly bread no chicken. Crab rangoon was tastless. I took one bite of the egg roll and automatically spit it out because it smelled sour...like I might get food poisoning. What a waste of money
Great deal. The jalapeño chicken was great and big portion. First time here will come back.
bad food
Good lunch specials.
Good food, reasonable prices

Where do I begin, I am very disappointed and feel very disrespected by the woman who answer the phone at 9on 5/1/2018. She hung up on me after I tried to understand her saying that my address was too far. She also had an attitude on the phone after I asked questions.

Been going to this place for a while now. While I love the food from another nearby Chinese restaurant much more, my wife sometimes prefers China Hut. I have never had a bad experience here. The food is always fresh and the staff is friendly.
Bad food. Will not return.

This place is very tired I order a large amount of food that was nasty not enough meat nothing but rice the chicken and beef were cut so small you weren't even sure what you were eating all I can say is go pass this place because over thirty dollars is to much for just to eat under cooked rice I give them a zero save your money not a good cook at this location

Amazing food. The pork chop was different than other Chinese place, not breaded too thick which was good and the garlic and jalapeno make the pork chop delicious. Chicken fried rice was decent and even small size was kinda filling. First time ordering, overall good experience.
I eat there today  the chicken was trouble I ate about 10 bites and tossed it out came home and got sick never again will I eat there
Great sesame chicken. Nice and crispy. Best lo mein I've ever had in town. Delivery was fast. First experience was overall wonderful. Will order again.

Ordered the General Tso's chicken small party tray. It arrived 44 minutes after placing my order which is the only reason I'm giving them this much stars. The chicken was not crispy, lacked sauce and was too oily. Will not order again

I'm sure take out food is just wonderful however, my review is based on eating at the restaurant.  At first glance, I felt as if this was a warm and inviting place but, that soon changed when I placed my order. I was informed that there would be an additional charge if I used a credit card. When I received my meal it was in a plastic container with plastic silverware. (Somewhat strange for a dine-in experience)...  This isn't necessarily a bad thing but, I was expecting something a little bit different..
Good food, well prepared and diverse. Unfortunately they miss the mark with their soup, and the chicken can be rubbery, but their jumbo shrimp egg foo young rocks.
Great food and nice service!  Ordered Orange Chicken and Combination LobMein, are surprisingly good. will for sure come back again to try out other dishes.

Great good. Fast service. Ordered a lot of food over the phone and came in after 15 minutes and the food was ready! I didn't know this place was busy until I saw the cashier was on the phone all the time. They must have a lot delivery orders. I love their mango pineapple smoothie! Strong mango and pineapple flavor and they use a lot of real fruit I can actually tasted it. Not too much sugar added to and it's only$3.25. I usually order bubble tea from China town and they are all expensive. Once I got a green bubble tea for $5.10. I was so pleased when I found out this China Hut having a wonderful smoothie with bubble! I don't need to go to china town for bubble tea anymore. Combination fried rice was great and the amount was generous. Jalapeño chicken was an art work. Wonderful spicy and sweet dish without much sauce. Will be back.

Fast and delicious. Ordered delivery on a Sunday night, it only took 40 mins although I live three blocks away. I've ordered a lot delivery in this neighborhood, usually would take an hour, but China Hut was really quick. I ordered another delivery last night and It took 50 mins, I guess it really depends on the traffic but the food was still hot and fresh. Jalapeño chicken was absolutely great and the crab Rangoon was good. The smoothie was really fruity and tasted. What really touched me was that they wrap my smoothie into a bag full filled with a lot ice to keep the smoothie fresh. It was SO NICE.

I can't believe this place is hiding in the street mall for so many years. My girl friend was doing the pedicure next store and I was bored and craving for Chinese. People work in the nail store told me there was a Chinese place next to them. I went right in and I found out this place has the best crab Rangoon and Mongolian beef! And their General Tsao's chicken was delicious, looked little darker than other place but tasted really good, I could eat two large rice with the chicken. I also ordered some combination fried rice for my girl friend and she ate it all and she also had few bits of my General chicken and she just wanted more. We don't live nearby but they deliver! I definitely will order the delivery from them later.

Terrible food have been ordering from them for 2 years and the last 2 times I've ordered from them my food has been completely not what I ordered and completely different than it was the last time there's no consistency.  When I call to talk to them about it they tell me I'm wrong that this is how they've always done it ....I would not recommend this place to anyone there are so many better Chinese restaurants out there stay away from this one, I will never order from them again

ordered a lot food and they gave me a free sample of their new item. some kind of spicy chicken, forgot the name but it was pretty good. The Mongolian beef and Chicken Lo mein was good and I just love their crab Rangoon.
Let just say they even charge 15cents for sweet & sour sauce even if u get a meal. Don't ask for spicy they over do it so u can by more to drink .

The service is good, but my order was not the one I asked for and when I speak on the phone I just said I'm sorry that for the next time say exactly what I wanted and I told him that it was extra hot, and the chicken could not find it . So many green peppers. Very bad place, very bad experience they believe that with just a thank you they fix everything
Good food and great lunch specials
The crab rangoon was pretty good.
Close to my work we order all the time! Very good food.
The fried rice was okay not bad but the Mongolia beef had no flavor and kinda dry wasn't too happy. When it first opened was great not anymore
Love the teriyaki chicken!
Fantastic food ！sesame chicken is so good！would come back again。

Terrible service and mediocre food.  Called for pickup and after constantly being put on hold and hung up on I got my order through. It then took me another hour and a half to get my food, which was the blandest Chinese food I've ever had.  Never going back.
I love this place! Their quick and my dishes are always cooked fresh
Best Chinese food in Lincoln Square/Andersonville!
Best Chinese food .. I been ordering from this place for the past 3 years and haven't got tired of it ..
